column5: Is anyone else considering going into this great long standing tournament!  http://www.quinte.com/walleye/findingwalleye.html  I can't wait until walleye opening day, getting back out on the lake and chasing down a winner.....never had the opportunity to register one bigger than 8 lbs during the tourny... with my fishing partner Jen, this year could be the one...
Good luck to you and jen dont forget to bring the Yo-zirs and Tail Dancers ..
It is going to be an amazing weekend of fishing I am sure... although, careful what you wish for!  What happens cousin, if my fish is bigger?  Can't wait!  Jen
I am thinking of it...havent done it in years since I lived in Belleville. Maybe my daughter and I will go after the pike category.
Easton I will be there ,this will be my second year at this amazing tournament maybe we will see you and Jen there.I will be staying at Bayside Cottages.MTP
There would be nothing more I would like better than to have you catch the bigger fish Jen....Thats just the way I am.....

We will be in Napanee you are a little further at the top of the bay. We will be in the same area.. Good spot. I wish you all the best. As as read earlier apparently Jen is catching the biggest fish...Or at least bigger than mine.
don't forget guys i'll be there too!!!,,,i'v already got the spots marked on my new gps!!!,,jen might catch one bigger then your but not bigger then mine!!! lol
Will be a good weekend of fishing! All competition aside! (who am I kidding, not in my family)
